WEBVTT

00:00.280 --> 00:01.931
<i>Previously on "For the People"...</i>

00:01.966 --> 00:04.188
Your client tried to blow up the
Statue of Liberty, Sandra Bell.

00:04.213 --> 00:07.852
We the jury find the
defendant, Mohammed Fayed, guilty.

00:07.886 --> 00:09.086
You could be a good lawyer.

00:09.121 --> 00:11.088
If you tried. You're just not trying.

00:11.123 --> 00:13.257
My tradition is now to eat with you

00:13.292 --> 00:15.426
every night before
the first day of trial.

00:15.461 --> 00:17.228
Can I get your number?

00:17.263 --> 00:19.096
I like you.

00:19.131 --> 00:20.560
This could never work.

00:20.595 --> 00:23.166
We'd be lying in bed,
and I'd be infuriated.

00:23.202 --> 00:24.400
My takeaway from that is that

00:24.436 --> 00:26.168
you've thought about us lying in bed.

00:26.204 --> 00:28.170
How is it that your first time on duty,

00:28.206 --> 00:29.239
you get him?

00:29.274 --> 00:31.374
I'd like for you to come by
my office this afternoon

00:31.409 --> 00:32.442
so we can discuss some things.

00:32.476 --> 00:34.277
- It's a date.
- It's not a date.

00:34.312 --> 00:36.246
- Do you miss him?
- Sometimes.

00:36.281 --> 00:38.348
This is the United States District Court

00:38.383 --> 00:40.250
for the Southern District of New York.

00:40.285 --> 00:41.608
Are you worthy?

00:44.655 --> 00:46.221
Do you hate me?

00:47.190 --> 00:48.089
Why would I hate you?

00:48.125 --> 00:49.864
It wasn't that bad. I mean, it wasn't...

00:49.899 --> 00:51.126
No, not that.

00:51.161 --> 00:53.629
I mean, you said we'd end up
in bed next to each other

00:53.664 --> 00:54.630
with you hating me.

00:54.665 --> 00:56.197
Oh, yeah, right.

00:56.233 --> 00:58.332
Well, yes. Give it time.

00:58.368 --> 01:00.801
But for right now...

01:00.836 --> 01:01.769
it's fun.

